channel_description:
Conferred City status on the 15th day of August 2024, Eldoret is located in western Kenya, south of Cherangany Hills.  The town came into being in the year 1910 with the construction of a post office on a site, which was known to the white settlers as Farm 64, 64 or Sisibo. The locals at that time referred to the town as Farm 64 or Sisibo because, the town of Eldoret was 64 miles away from the newly established Uganda Railway railhead, located at Kibigori.

Bethel Studios KE prides in documenting and sharing the rich life and history of Eldoret ranging from politics, healthcare, education, art, business, farming, athletics and many more aspects of the great Eldoret City. 

Please write to us on bethelstudioske@gmail.com or call 0723433576 for a feature in this podcast.

The Catholic Nurses Association of Kenya (CNAK) started in 1981 as Caritas Nurses Association of Kenya. It was established through the support of the Caritas Nurses of Germany and with the effort of the late His Eminence Cardinal Maurice Otunga.

Members of the association come from public and private health facilities, Faith Based organizations, private and retired nurse practitioners. Members of the
association come from branches throughout the country and the headquarters are in Nairobi. CNAK is a member of the International Committee of Nurses and Medical Social Assistants (CICIAMS)

The organization aims to bring together healthcare workers including nurses of the Catholic faith to unite and strengthen each other spiritually, socially and professionally. Members of CNAK view their work as a service to Christ whom they encounter in all the sick, poor, helpless, despised, underprivileged and persecuted in the community.
